The paper deals with the influence maximization problem in social networks, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of several CS sub-disciplines. The most likely category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), which is specifically focused on the study of social networks and their properties. The second likely category is cs.SOC (Computational Social Science), which deals with the application of computational methods to social science research. The third likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), which is relevant because the paper proposes new algorithms for solving the influence maximization problem. The fourth likely category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), which is relevant because the paper proposes a new definition of the influence maximization problem that takes into account the time taken for influence propagation. The fifth likely category is cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity), which is relevant because the paper discusses the impact of network evolution on the quality of selected seeds.
